Nebraska’s Jordan Westerkamp tries to run past a Southern Miss defender on Sept. 26. The Huskers host Wisconsin on Saturday. (Corbey R. Dorsey / For The North Platte Telegraph) Posted: Friday, October 9, 2015 1:41 pm Huskers say they’re ready for Wisconsin run game this time Associated Press | 
LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) — Nebraska knows what’s coming and believes it’s ready. 
The Cornhuskers knew last year, too, but definitely weren’t prepared for Wisconsin’s Melvin Gordon to run for an FBS-record 408 yards and four touchdowns in a demoralizing 35-point loss in Madison.   Need an account? Create one now. Subscription required
